This is a support library for the Sino:bit, the BBC Micro:bit inspired board designed and developed by Naomi Wu and Elecrow.

Written by Dave Astels for Adafruit Industries. MIT license, check LICENSE for more information.
All text above must be included in any redistribution.

Place the Sinobit library folder your arduinosketchfolder/libraries/ folder. You may need to create the libraries subfolder if its your first library. Restart the IDE.

Also requires the Adafruit_GFX (https://github.com/adafruit/Adafruit-GFX-Library) and HT1632 (https://github.com/adafruit/HT1632) libraries for Arduino.
